A '''brush hook''' (also called a '''bush hook''', '''ditch blade''', '''ditch bank blade''', or '''ditch blade axe''') is a [[gardening]] instrument resembling an [[axe]], generally with a {{convert|12|in|cm|adj=on}} to {{convert|16|in|cm|adj=on}} curved [[blade]] and a {{convert|36|in|cm|adj=on}} to {{convert|48|in|cm|adj=on}} handle.  It is commonly used by [[surveying]] crews and [[firefighter]]s to clear out heavy [[undergrowth]] from trails, as well as by homeowners and gardeners to clear thick brush.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.americantrails.org/resources/info/tools3.html |first=Jim |last=Schmid |title=Brushing Tools |work=Tools for Trail Work |publisher=AmericanTrails.org |accessdate=2009-02-07}}</ref>

