'''''Development Driller III''''' is a fifth generation, [[Vanuatu]]-[[flag of convenience|flagged]] [[dynamic positioning]] [[semi-submersible]] ultra-deepwater drilling rig owned by [[Transocean]] and operated under lease agreements by various petroleum exploration and production companies worldwide. The vessel is capable of drilling in water depths up to {{convert|7500|ft}} with drilling depth of {{convert|35000|ft}}, upgradeable to {{convert|37500|ft}}.<ref>{{cite web | title=''Development Driller III'' | url=http://www.deepwater.com/fw/main/Development-Driller-III-424C17.html?LayoutID=17 | publisher=Transocean | accessdate=9 June 2010}}</ref>

On May 2, 2010, ''Development Driller III'' started drilling a relief well on [[Macondo Prospect]] to stop [[Deepwater Horizon oil spill|massive oil spill]] caused by the [[Deepwater Horizon drilling rig explosion|explosion and subsequent loss]] of the ''[[Deepwater Horizon]]''.<ref name=upstream170510>{{cite news | url = http://www.upstreamonline.com/live/article215111.ece | title = Second Macondo relief well under way | newspaper = [[Upstream (newspaper)|Upstream Online]] | publisher = NHST Media Group | date = 2010-05-17 | accessdate = 2010-05-25}}</ref>

